<br>
But they also show where the discontent for uber level 60 druids come from.<br>
<br>
Also I do agree that this first fact gathering step,,,should be devoid of regen abilities.  The facts provided by Tudamorf and others should really be contained in a different thread.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of variables as I see it,,,dividing up the numbers for fast heals, regens, &amp; class comparisons first seems like a good idea at this point.  Mixing them all together here,,,right now,,,seems like a jumble to me,,,and not very cogent.<br>
<br>
Each by itself where we can then make clearer conclusions would make more sense.<br>
<br>
I do think that this part of the experiment is done, and does show that a 55 druid is still healing pretty much the same as a level 40.  A conclusion that I for one did not expect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#333399>- </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove>The Druids Grove</a><font color=#333399> - </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm18>FAQ & Index</a> <font color=#333399> - </font><a href="http://www.thedruidsgrove.org">The Druids Grove</a><font color=#333399> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.4.7<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

